   {:e #blake3 "34ab80a8806c0bab3483729b4fb97d911f4755d6cc7e77a20f31e5dc9409deff" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "REVISED DESIGN: Instead of a new EvidenceLevel enum, EXTEND the existing provenance lattice + witness depth system. The evidence strength of a datom = provenance_type_weight × verification_depth_weight × freshness_decay. This uses: (1) ProvenanceType from ADR-STORE-008 (already implemented — observed=1.0, derived=0.8, inferred=0.5, hypothesized=0.2). (2) Witness verification depth from INV-WITNESS-002 (spec exists, partially implemented — L1..L4). (3) Observation freshness from ADR-HARVEST-005 (spec exists, partially implemented — per-namespace TTL). The COMPOSITE evidence strength for boundary checking becomes: evidence(d) = provenance_weight(d) × depth_factor(d) × freshness(d). This is computed by the boundary framework at check time — NOT stored as a new attribute. No new schema needed. No new resolution mode needed. The provenance lattice IS the evidence lattice. We just need to wire it into the BoundaryCheck framework.; Session entity: :task/t-efa31fb3; Session entity: :task/t-1df529fa; Session entity: :task/t-ff6a4143; Session entity: :task/t-e31c20ca; Session entity: :task/t-b489c254; Session entity: :task/t-fdb83aaa; Session entity: :task/t-e225ba30; Session entity: :task/t-6ed15191; Session entity: :task/t-497f67a4; Session entity: :task/t-53cc69f9; Session entity: :task/t-411add92; Session entity: :task/t-d336e641; Session entity: :task/t-7ee28e62; GAP ANALYSIS — Missing tasks from the three workstreams: WORKSTREAM A (Boundary Framework): BOUNDARY-1..10 exist. Gap: no task for the ACTUAL BoundaryCheck implementations beyond SpecImplBoundary and ImplEntryBoundary. Need: SchemaUsageBoundary (declared attrs vs used attrs), TestCoverageBoundary (tested components vs total components), TaskSpecBoundary (tasks trace to specs). Each is a concrete BoundaryCheck impl that exercises the framework. WORKSTREAM B (Substrate-Agnostic): SUBSTRATE-1..8 + EXTRACTOR-1..7 exist. Gap: no task for evidence lattice schema (:evidence/level attribute), no task for lattice resolution mode on evidence attributes, no task for evidence-weighted F(S) computation. WORKSTREAM C (MCP Continuous Extraction): Zero implementation tasks. Need: MCP extraction layer design, behavioral signal taxonomy, automatic datom production from tool calls, evidence=0.2 tagging, integration with harvest pipeline. CROSS-CUTTING: No task for the UNIFIED integration test that verifies the full loop: extractor → datoms → boundary → F(S) → guidance → agent action → re-extract → F(S) improves.; Session entity: :task/t-88794860; SESSION 026 COMPREHENSIVE REVIEW — Three architectural breakthroughs this session: (1) TOPOLOGY COMPILATION PIPELINE: quick_plan implemented and self-bootstrapped. 35 tasks closed. But the SPECTRAL path (density matrix eigendecomposition → Fiedler partition) is specified but unimplemented. The Quick path uses connected components (O(n)); Spectral uses eigendecomposition (O(n³)) for OPTIMAL partitioning. (2) GENERALIZED BOUNDARY FRAMEWORK: BoundaryCheck trait parameterizes the bilateral loop. Spec complete (INV-BILATERAL-007..009, ADR-BILATERAL-005..006, NEG-BILATERAL-003..004). Tasks created (BOUNDARY-1..10). Implementation not started. (3) SUBSTRATE-AGNOSTIC EXTRACTOR ARCHITECTURE: Store-as-DI, extractors-as-datoms, evidence lattice, MCP continuous extraction. Spec complete (INV-FOUNDATION-001..005, ADR-FOUNDATION-007..011, NEG-FOUNDATION-001..002). Tasks partially created (SUBSTRATE-1..8, EXTRACTOR-1..7). GAP: No tasks yet for evidence lattice implementation, MCP extraction layer, or the cross-cutting integration between all three workstreams.; Session entity: :task/t-90b7d513; Session entity: :task/t-6169f35e; CRITICAL RECONCILIATION: The evidence lattice (INV-FOUNDATION-005) MUST be reconciled with existing provenance lattice (ADR-STORE-008: observed=1.0, derived=0.8, inferred=0.5, hypothesized=0.2) and witness verification depth (INV-WITNESS-002: L1=comments, L2=unit tests, L3=proptests, L4=formal proofs) and uncertainty tensor (ADR-UNCERTAINTY-001: sigma_e, sigma_a, sigma_c) and resolution contribution weighting (ADR-RESOLUTION-012: unverified=1, witnessed=2, challenged=3). These are FOUR existing graduated confidence systems. The evidence lattice I proposed is a FIFTH. This is WRONG — it should be a UNIFICATION of the existing four, not a new parallel system. The correct design: EvidenceLevel IS the provenance type × verification depth × resolution weight. It's a COMPOSITE, not a new primitive. The witness system's L1-L4 levels ARE the evidence lattice — we just need to extend them to non-witness entities.\nSession entity: :task/t-80e061b7; Session entity: :task/t-4a5a2e48; Session entity: :task/t-150bf6dd; Session entity: :task/t-8658eb77; Session entity: :task/t-d8bc1f0c; Session entity: :task/t-40314c12; Session entity: :task/t-42a1a89b; Session entity: :task/t-053e1287; Session entity: :task/t-cad805e9; Session entity: :task/t-7da6077b; Session entity: :task/t-ea6d8241" :op :assert}
